text: Alec Marks (10 December 1910 - 28 July 1983) was an Australian cricketer. He played 35 first-class matches for New South Wales between 1928/29 and 1936/37. ==See also== * List of New South Wales representative cricketers ==References== ==External links== * Category:1910 births Category:1983 deaths Category:Australian cricketers Category:New South Wales cricketers Category:Cricketers from Brisbane
